quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  42,45,"And you will see them being exposed to it [i.e., the Fire], humbled from humiliation, looking from [behind] a covert glance. And those who had believed will say, \"Indeed, the [true] losers are the ones who lost themselves and their families on the Day of Resurrection. Unquestionably, the wrongdoers are in an enduring punishment.\"",""
  42,46,"And there will not be for them any allies to aid them other than Allāh. And whoever Allāh sends astray - for him there is no way.",""
  42,47,"Respond to your Lord before a Day comes from Allāh of which there is no repelling. No refuge will you have that Day, nor for you will there be any denial.[1]","[1] Of your sins or \"disapproval\" of your punishment."
  42,48,"But if they turn away - then We have not sent you, [O Muḥammad], over them as a guardian; upon you is only [the duty of] notification. And indeed, when We let man taste mercy from Us, he rejoices in it; but if evil afflicts him for what his hands have put forth, then indeed, man is ungrateful.",""
  42,49,"To Allāh belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth; He creates what He wills. He gives to whom He wills female [children], and He gives to whom He wills males.",""
  42,50,"Or He makes them [both] males and females, and He renders whom He wills barren. Indeed, He is Knowing and Competent.",""
  42,51,"And it is not for any human being that Allāh should speak to him except by revelation or from behind a partition or that He sends a messenger [i.e., angel] to reveal, by His permission, what He wills. Indeed, He is Most High and Wise.",""
